column1: Task 1: In the ‘Wrong flags per time played’ view, identify the most appropriate elbow method number in the helper elbow chart.
column2: Task 2: In the 'Wrong flags per time played' view (for all levels), do you see any suspicious trainees? Why/why not? If so, what is the trainee ID?
column3: Task 3: In the 'Wrong flags per time played' view (for level 5), what could the results imply regarding the level design?
column4: Task 4: In the 'Time spent after using the hint' view (for all levels), what does the point distribution suggest? Does it imply a good training design or bad?
column5: Task 5: In the 'Behavior correlation chart' (for all levels),  are there any clusters that represent distinct strategies but share similar training success ?
column6: Task 6: In the 'Behavior correlation chart' (for all levels), are there any possible outliers ?
column7: Task 7: In the 'Behavior correlation chart', how variable is overal success of the trainees accross the clusters?
column8: Task 8: In the dataset of 'Hacking Day Cyber Task Force Delta' (all levels), determine which strategy (which cluster of trainees) was the most successful?
